# Documentation Patterns

## Documentation Structure
- **Architecture**: [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) - System design and components
- **Development**: [DEVELOPMENT.md](mdc:docs/DEVELOPMENT.md) - Development workflow and setup
- **Performance**: [PERFORMANCE_GUIDE.md](mdc:docs/PERFORMANCE_GUIDE.md) - Performance optimization
- **Quality Standards**: [QUALITY_STANDARDS.md](mdc:docs/QUALITY_STANDARDS.md) - Code quality standards
- **Quality Gates**: [QUALITY_GATES_GUIDE.md](mdc:docs/QUALITY_GATES_GUIDE.md) - Quality gates system
- **Commit Troubleshooting**: [COMMIT_TROUBLESHOOTING.md](mdc:docs/COMMIT_TROUBLESHOOTING.md) - Commit issue resolution
- **Documentation Guide**: [DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md) - Comprehensive documentation standards

## Writing Standards
- **Pattern**: Clear headings, code examples, cross-references
- **Format**: Use `##` for main sections, `###` for subsections
- **Links**: Use `[text](mdc:docs/FILE.md#section)` for internal documentation
- **Code**: Use triple backticks with language specification
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#writing-standards)

## Content Guidelines
- **Pattern**: User-centered design, clear language, active voice
- **Structure**: Introduction, main content, examples, references
- **Examples**: Realistic examples from codebase, tested and verified
- **Avoid**: Static performance metrics, specific timing numbers, version-specific performance data
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#content-guidelines)

## Docstring Format
- **Pattern**: Google-style docstrings with Args, Returns, Raises
- **Format**: Triple quotes, clear descriptions, type hints
- **Example**: Document all public functions and classes
- **Reference**: [Quality Standards Guide](mdc:docs/QUALITY_STANDARDS.md#documentation-standards)

## Code Examples
- **Pattern**: Realistic examples from codebase, tested and working
- **Format**: Include comments, show expected output
- **Context**: Provide setup and usage context
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#code-examples)

## Maintenance Procedures
- **Pattern**: Update documentation with code changes
- **Process**: Plan, write, review, test, maintain
- **Triggers**: Code changes, new features, bug fixes, user feedback
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#maintenance-procedures)

## Quality Assurance
- **Pattern**: Regular reviews, accuracy checks, user feedback
- **Tools**: Automated checks, manual reviews, user testing
- **Standards**: Accuracy, completeness, clarity, consistency
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#quality-assurance)

## Troubleshooting Documentation
- **Pattern**: Problem description, solution steps, prevention strategies
- **Format**: Clear headings, step-by-step procedures, code examples
- **Context**: Include when to use, alternatives, common issues
- **Reference**: [Commit Troubleshooting Guide](mdc:docs/COMMIT_TROUBLESHOOTING.md)

## Documentation Types
- **Architecture**: System design, components, data flow
- **Development**: Setup, workflow, contributing guidelines
- **Performance**: Optimization techniques, benchmarks, monitoring
- **Quality**: Standards, testing, quality gates
- **Troubleshooting**: Common issues, solutions, prevention
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#documentation-types)
